Sieve GUI for macOS — License Status
=====================================

> Project state: Pre-GA (private repo, public at GA together with sieve daemon).
> Linked decisions: sieve daemon ADR-011 (private until GA) / ADR-029 (free-first).

This repository contains TWO categories of content with DIFFERENT license terms,
mirroring the sieve daemon repository (../sieve/LICENSE).

---

## 1. Documentation

Scope: `docs/`, `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`, `CLAUDE.md`, `tasks/PROGRESS.md`,
       `tasks/lessons.md`, and any other Markdown / config files NOT inside the
       Swift source tree.

License: **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International
         (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)**
URL:     https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/4.0/

You are free to:

  - Share — copy and redistribute in any medium or format
  - Adapt — remix, transform, build upon

Under the following terms:

  - Attribution — credit to "Sieve project" with link to the upstream repo
  - NonCommercial — not for commercial purposes (commercial reuse requires
    written permission: doskey.lee@gmail.com)
  - ShareAlike — derivatives must use the same license

Rationale: GUI documentation includes architecture, IPC contract, ADRs, and
HIPS UX design rationale. These are "trust artifacts" — published at GA so
users can verify the security model before installing the binary, but should
not be repackaged as competitor material without permission.

---

## 2. Source Code

Scope: All Swift source code under `Sources/`, `Tests/`, `Package.swift`,
       `project.yml`, `config/Info.plist`, `config/SieveGUI.entitlements`,
       `appcast.xml`, `scripts/`, and any Swift / shell / configuration files
       required to build and ship the macOS app.

License: **MIT License** — see Section 4 below for the full text.

The MIT terms apply at GA (when the repository is made public). Pre-GA the
repository is private and not licensed for redistribution.

---

## 3. Trademarks

"Sieve" is the project codename. See ../sieve/LICENSE §3 for trademark notes
that apply equally to GUI assets (icon, app name, menu-bar branding).

Use of the name "Sieve" or the Sieve menu-bar icon for derivative products
requires written permission.

